<LegalPage
  lang="en"
  pageKey="about"
  title="About PoolPilot"
  description="What PoolPilot is, why it exists — and the clear note: an independent project, not affiliated with Pool Digital GmbH."
  lead="An independent one-person project from Germany."
>
  <h2>What it's about</h2>
  <p>
    PoolPilot brings your pool controller to iPhone, iPad, Apple Watch and Android as a proper, native
    app. Instead of a clunky web interface you get clear gauges, fast switches and widgets — one app
    that works with both the ProCon.IP and the Violet, detecting which controller you have automatically.
  </p>

  <h2>Why PoolPilot exists</h2>
  <p>
    The project grew out of wanting to comfortably read and operate one's own pool controller from the
    couch. It is built in spare time by a single person — with a lot of care, but without a big company
    behind it.
  </p>

  <h2>How we handle data</h2>
  <p>
    No accounts, no ads, no tracking. The app talks directly to your controller on your own network;
    credentials stay on your device. Details are in the
    <a href={path('privacy', 'en')}>Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Independence and trademarks</h2>
  <p>
    PoolPilot is an <strong>independent project</strong> and is not affiliated with Pool Digital GmbH —
    not sponsored, endorsed or reviewed by them. The names “ProCon.IP” and “Violet” and related
    trademarks belong to their respective owners and are used solely to describe which hardware PoolPilot
    works with.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions, requests or a problem? The <a href={path('support', 'en')}>help page</a> shows the
    quickest way.
  </p>
</LegalPage>
